Let $S = \omega^{16} + \omega^{18} + \omega^{20} + \dots + \omega^{54}.$  This is a geometric series with first term $a = \omega^{16},$ common ratio $r = \omega^2,$ and number of terms $n = \frac{54 - 16}{2} + 1 = \frac{38}{2} + 1 = 19 + 1 = 20.$  Then
\begin{align*} S &= \frac{\omega^{16} (1 - (\omega^2)^{20})}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= \frac{\omega^{16} (1 - \omega^{40})}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= \frac{\omega^{16} (1 - \omega^{5 \cdot 7 + 5})}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= \frac{\omega^{16} (1 - \omega^5)}{1 - \omega^2}. \end{align*}Since $\omega^7 = 1,$ $\omega^{16} = \omega^{2 \cdot 7 + 2} = \omega^2.$  Then
\begin{align*} S &= \frac{\omega^2 (1 - \omega^5)}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= \frac{\omega^2 - \omega^7}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= \frac{\omega^2 - 1}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= -1. \end{align*}

The sum is
\begin{align*} \omega^{16} + \omega^{18} + \omega^{20} + \dots + \omega^{54} &= \sum_{n=8}^{27} \omega^{2n} \\ &= \sum_{n=8}^{27} (\omega^2)^n \\ &= \frac{(\omega^2)^8 (1 - (\omega^2)^{20})}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= \frac{\omega^{16} (1 - \omega^{40})}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= \frac{\omega^2 (1 - \omega^5)}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= \frac{\omega^2 - \omega^7}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= \frac{\omega^2 - 1}{1 - \omega^2} \\ &= -1. \end{align*}

The final answer is $\boxed{-1}$
